English(英語)
1. Philosophy of Personal Information Protection
(1)  Live2D Inc. (hereinafter referred to as “Live2D”) acknowledges the importance and social responsibility of protecting personal information well, and handles personal information entrusted to us in a strict manner paying close attention.
(2) Live2D will acquire personal information only within the scope of the purpose of acquisition after specifying it. Live2D will use personal information only within the scope of the purpose of acquisition, and will not use it for any other purpose.
(3) Live2D shall endeavor to protect personal information by clarifying the rules for handling personal information and making every employee informed the rules. Live2D will take the necessary measures to prevent the leakage or loss of personal information, and manage it appropriately.
2. Purpose of Use
Where Live2D acquires personal information, Live2D will use it only within the scope of the purposes specified below, and will not use it beyond the scope of legitimate purposes without the consent of the individual. However, this does not apply to legal requests cases, emergencies such as life threatening or public health improvement, or other cases permitted by law.
(1)  Sales activities for Live2D’s services and products (planning, development, sales, provision, support, maintenance, etc.)
(2) Promotions for Live2D’s services and products (PR, campaigns, events, questionnaire surveys, etc.)
(3) Communication related to Live2D’s services and products (provision of information, order placement, billing, receipt and payment, response to inquiries, etc.)
(4) Personnel labor management, such as hiring or recruiting employees (including applicants for employment and retired employees)
(5) Carrying out other operations related to operations set forth in the preceding items.
3. Provision to A Third Party
Live2D may outsource part of its operation to implement the operation smoothly. In this case, Live2D will take necessary and appropriate measures to protect personal information, such as concluding a contract with the subcontractor regarding handling of the personal information. In addition to providing personal information to the subcontractors, Live2D may provide personal information to third parties only;
(1) If Live2D obtains the prior consent of the person;
(2) If Live2D is required by law or court order;
(3) In the case of succession of business due to merger, corporate separation, business transfer or other reasons;
(4) Cases in which the handling of the personal information is necessary for the protection of the life, body, or property of an individual and in which it is difficult to obtain the consent of the person;
(5) Cases in which the disclosing or providing information in a manner that does not identify the individual such as statistical data format;
(6) Cases in which the cooperation with execution of affairs prescribed by laws and/or regulations by a state organ, a local government is required and in which obtaining the consent of the person is likely to impede the execution of the affairs concerned; and
(7) Cases permitted by law and/or regulations or based on legitimate reasons.
Notwithstanding the foregoing, even in the case of outsourcing or the cases stipulated in the above subsections of this Section 3, Live2D will not disclose information acquired from Apple Inc. “TrueDepth API” to any third party.
4. Inquiries about Disclosure, Correction, Deletion, etc. of Personal Information
Live2D will disclose, correct, delete, etc. personal information Live2D possess within a reasonable period of time and scope upon request from the person or its representative. If you wish to disclose, correct, delete, etc. your personal data, please contact our contact in charge. Note that Live2D may verify personal identification of the person or its representative, and/or your trading records with Live2D.
5. Application and Changes
This Privacy Policy applies only to personal information acquired by Live2D. Live2D may modify this Privacy Policy from time to time for reasons such as revisions of laws or attempt to improve the protection measures of personal information, and the modified Privacy Policy will be effective on the date posted on Live2D’s website. Since Live2D is not responsible for protections of privacy under other websites linked to Live2D's website, confirmation of the privacy policies of those websites is highly recommended.
6. Use of Cookies
Live2D uses Cookie on Live2D’s website.  With regard to nizima Live TRACKER, in no case, Live2D acquires your personal information through Cookie.
7. Request to You
(1) In order to prevent others from accessing your personal information and communication records, please log out always after logging in and accessing to Live2D’s services in each case. Also, please keep your password and membership information confidential. If your account has been illegally accessed, please contact us immediately.
(2) Live2D shall not be responsible for any personal contact information that is disclosed by you actively for the purpose of informing other customers who use Live2D services. Please disclose personal information within the scope of your own responsibility by setting and managing the disclosure level by yourself. Please note that any personal information you disclose may be collected and used by others.
8. About nizima LIVE TRACKER
Infromation Used by nizima LIVE TRACKER:
nizima LIVE TRACKER application does not collect user information. nizima LIVE TRACKER acquires information and facial expression data obtained from Apple Inc. “TrueDepth API” only if permitted by users, uses such information and data only when they are reflected to motion of Live2D model and does not store or execute similar processings on  such information and data.
Data Sharing:
nizima LIVE TRACKER does not share the information obtained from “TrueDepth API” to Live2D or  a third party.  When “PC connection” function for  communicating with nizima LIVE (Windows) is activated, the information obtained from “TrueDepth API” is transmitted to IP address in local network input on the application.
Access and Suspension of Data Collection:
Permission with regard to data acquisition by nizima LIVE TRACKER can be turned off through iPhone setting  at any time.  By uninstalling this application from the terminal device in use, acquisition and transmission of information can be suspended.
Consent Acquisition:
Please use nizima LIVE TRACKER after checking and consenting to this Privacy Policy.  When you use this application, you are deemed to have agreed with this Privacy Policy.
